26/07/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The Macedonian co-ordination committee for crisis management was inaugurated Monday (25 July), at a ceremony attended by Deputy Prime Minister Musa Xhaferri, Interior Minister Ljubomir Mihajlovski, Defence Minister Jovan Manasievski and State Security and Counterintelligence Chief Mile Zecevic. The new body will be tasked with implementing new crisis management legislation, and will act in close co-operation with a newly-established security risk assessment group. (Macedonian Government Web site - 26/07/05)
